<br>
While attending the Central Arizona College, Ben Pearson completed a study of Orion and was in email contact with George Dyson.<br>
<br>
The Orion project team requested $30 Mill. from Congress to continue development along with some underground nuclear testing. Congress saw no practical use for Orion and instead gave them $100,000 and handed the project over to the newly formed NASA agency. NASA had their sites on the moon using chemical rockets and was not about to take any chances on a nuclear propelled spacecraft with design flaws. That was the end of funding for Orion.<br>
